verses.verse: For the Chief Musician. A Psalm. A Song of David. <S%H8416>Praise<s%> <S%H1747>waiteth<s%> for <S%H430>thee<s%>, O God, in <S%H6726>Zion<s%>; And unto thee shall the <S%H5088>vow<s%> be <S%H7999>performed<s%>.
O thou that <S%H8085>hearest<s%> <S%H8605>prayer<s%>, Unto thee shall all <S%H1320>flesh<s%> <S%H935>come<s%>.
Iniquities <S%H1697><s%> <S%H1396>prevail<s%> against <S%H6588>me<s%>: As for our transgressions, thou wilt forgive <S%H3722>them<s%>.

Blessed <S%H835><s%> is the man whom thou <S%H977>choosest<s%>, and causest to <S%H7126>approach<s%> unto <S%H7931>thee<s%>, That he may dwell in thy <S%H2691>courts<s%>: We shall be <S%H7646>satisfied<s%> with the <S%H2898>goodness<s%> of thy <S%H1004>house<s%>, Thy <S%H6918>holy<s%> <S%H1964>temple<s%>.

By terrible <S%H3372>things<s%> thou wilt <S%H6030>answer<s%> us in <S%H6664>righteousness<s%>, Oh <S%H430>God<s%> of our <S%H3468>salvation<s%>, Thou that art the <S%H4009>confidence<s%> of all the <S%H7099>ends<s%> of the <S%H776>earth<s%>, And of them that are afar <S%H7350>off<s%> upon the <S%H3220>sea<s%>:
Who by his <S%H3581>strength<s%> setteth <S%H3559>fast<s%> the <S%H2022>mountains<s%>, Being <S%H247>girded<s%> about with <S%H1369>might<s%>;
Who <S%H7623>stilleth<s%> the <S%H7588>roaring<s%> of the <S%H3220>seas<s%>, The <S%H7588>roaring<s%> of their <S%H1530>waves<s%>, And the <S%H1995>tumult<s%> of the <S%H3816>peoples<s%>.

They also that <S%H3427>dwell<s%> in the uttermost <S%H7099>parts<s%> are <S%H3372>afraid<s%> at thy <S%H226>tokens<s%>: Thou makest the <S%H4161>outgoings<s%> of the <S%H1242>morning<s%> and <S%H6153>evening<s%> to <S%H7442>rejoice<s%>.

Thou <S%H6485>visitest<s%> the <S%H776>earth<s%>, and <S%H7783>waterest<s%> <S%H7227>it<s%>, Thou greatly <S%H6238>enrichest<s%> <S%H6388>it<s%>; The river of <S%H430>God<s%> is <S%H4390>full<s%> of <S%H4325>water<s%>: Thou <S%H3559>providest<s%> them <S%H1715>grain<s%>, when thou hast so prepared the <S%H3559>earth<s%>.

Thou <S%H7301>waterest<s%> its <S%H1417>furrows<s%> <S%H7301>abundantly<s%>; Thou <S%H5181>settlest<s%> the <S%H8525>ridges<s%> <S%H4127>thereof<s%>: Thou makest it soft with <S%H7241>showers<s%>; Thou <S%H1288>blessest<s%> the springing <S%H6780>thereof<s%>.
Thou <S%H5849>crownest<s%> the <S%H8141>year<s%> with thy <S%H2896>goodness<s%>; And thy <S%H4570>paths<s%> <S%H7491>drop<s%> <S%H1880>fatness<s%>.
They <S%H7491>drop<s%> upon the <S%H4999>pastures<s%> of the <S%H4057>wilderness<s%>; And the <S%H1389>hills<s%> are <S%H2296>girded<s%> with <S%H1524>joy<s%>.

The <S%H3733>pastures<s%> are <S%H3847>clothed<s%> with <S%H6629>flocks<s%>; The <S%H6010>valleys<s%> also are covered <S%H5848>over<s%> with <S%H1250>grain<s%>; They shout for <S%H7321>joy<s%>, they also <S%H7891>sing<s%>.
